overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification. The agent meticulously
  analyzed the existing implementation against the acceptance criteria,
  identifying several critical gaps. Subsequently, the agent proceeded to
  implement these missing features. This included adding a 1-10 severity scale
  for tiredness with crucial safety warnings, integrating detection and tailored
  recommendations for COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and implementing a
  weighted scoring system for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness. Furthermore, the CSV
  export functionality was significantly enhanced to include all flattened
  questionnaire responses, and new questions were introduced to screen for pain
  affecting sleep and chronic fatigue symptoms, complete with relevant report
  logic and recommendations. The implementation involved systematic updates
  across data types, validation schemas, UI components, and both web and PDF
  report generation, ensuring a robust and feature-complete application.
